The '1955â56 FA Cup' was the 75th staging of the world's oldest cup competition,
the FA Cup. Manchester City won the competition, beating Birmingham City 3â1 in
the final at Wembley, London.

Matches were scheduled to be played at the stadium of the team named first on
the date specified for each round, which was always a Saturday. If scores were
level after 90 minutes had been played, a replay would take place at the stadium
of the second-named team later the same week. If the replayed match was drawn
further replays would be held at neutral venues until a winner was determined.
If scores were level after 90 minutes had been played in a replay, a 30-minute
period of extra time would be played.
